.SH NAME
.PP
twitch \[en] Twitch.tv client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]twitch\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]command\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Check live followed Twitch.tv channels and watch broadcasts using
\f[B]streamlink\f[R].
.PP
Configuration required for viewing your Twitch account\[cq]s followed
and live channels is automatically prompted for when required, and then
stored in \f[C]\[ti]/.twitch\f[R].
.PP
The program does not receive, or require, write or read access to your
account, but simply uses public-facing read-only API records.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \f[C]-h\f[R], \f[C]--help\f[R]
Print help.
.TP
.B \f[C]-v\f[R], \f[C]--version\f[R]
Print version number.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \f[C]following\f[R]
Lists followed channels.
.TP
.B \f[C]live\f[R]
Lists followed live channels.
.TP
.B \f[C]open\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]channel\f[R]\f[C]>\f[R]
Opens a channel page in \f[C]$BROWSER\f[R].
.TP
